{
  "stem": "10587.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when you fell down, he would take the shovel and place it across your neck and step on it on both sides.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This I have something new for me, a new title, and I've seen him do this quite a few times.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He was the Report Fuhrer and a Sturmbannfuhrer in charge of the inner-- inner-- in the-- like the fuhrer of the concentration camp inside-- not for daily operations.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he-- he would-- he would walk away from it, and it wouldn't even like-- wouldn't phase him, it wouldn't bother him, and maybe look for another, the next person to receive the same kind of a treatment.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And this was a daily routine concentration camp, a working concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Food was always a problem, never enough food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Cold was a problem, and the conditions were at least a little better than Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we-- I was there for a year and a few months.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, because my friends always were there to-- to help me out, because I-- I would not go to the infirmary.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- at one time I was terribly sick, and I was in-- in Funfteichen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think I must have had typhoid fever, and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and there was a doctor from my hometown that was working in the infirmary. but I went to see him.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But not as a-- I didn't want to stay there because they constantly used to take the people and clean out the infirmary, and send them to--",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To the gas chamber, but we did not-- I mean, to the-- to the crematoriums, but in Funfteichen, they would just transport their bodies somewheres to another camp, maybe Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
